"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The wrist is placed in neutral position, radial side up. Downward pressure is applied just proximal to the carpometacarpal joint of the thumb. With firm pressure applied to the anatomic snuff box, the rounded distal portion of the scaphoid (navicular) can be felt when the wrist is passively ulnar deviated.",
